1
0:00:12.996,000 --> 0:00:13,000
In June of 1998,

2
0:00:14.807,000 --> 0:00:19,000
Tori Murden McClure left Nags Head, North Carolina for France.

3
0:00:20.147,000 --> 0:00:22,000
That's her boat, the American Pearl.

4
0:00:22.469,000 --> 0:00:24,000
It's 23 feet long and just six feet across

5
0:00:24.913,000 --> 0:00:25,000
at its widest point.

6
0:00:26.881,000 --> 0:00:3,000
The deck was the size of a cargo bed of a Ford F-150 pickup truck.

7
0:00:31.873,000 --> 0:00:33,000
Tori and her friends built it by hand,

8
0:00:34.357,000 --> 0:00:36,000
and it weighed about 1,800 pounds.

9
0:00:37.051,000 --> 0:00:39,000
Her plan was to row it alone

10
0:00:39.414,000 --> 0:00:4,000
across the Atlantic Ocean --

11
0:00:41.364,000 --> 0:00:43,000
no motor, no sail --

12
0:00:43.5,000 --> 0:00:46,000
something no woman and no American had ever done before.

13
0:00:47.262,000 --> 0:00:48,000
This would be her route:

14
0:00:48.841,000 --> 0:00:52,000
over 3,600 miles across the open North Atlantic Ocean.

15
0:00:53.068,000 --> 0:00:55,000
Professionally, Tori worked as a project administrator

16
0:00:55.683,000 --> 0:00:56,000
for the city of Louisville, Kentucky,

17
0:00:57.478,000 --> 0:00:58,000
her hometown,

18
0:00:59.289,000 --> 0:01:01,000
but her real passion was exploring.

19
0:01:01.704,000 --> 0:01:03,000
This was not her first big expedition.

20
0:01:04.188,000 --> 0:01:08,000
Several years earlier, she'd become the first woman to ski to the South Pole.

21
0:01:08.554,000 --> 0:01:1,000
She was an accomplished rower in college,

22
0:01:10.783,000 --> 0:01:13,000
even competed for a spot on the 1992 U.S. Olympic team,

23
0:01:14.265,000 --> 0:01:17,000
but this, this was different.

24
