41
0:02:07.019,000 --> 0:02:11,000
DL: She saw fish, dolphins,

42
0:02:11.93,000 --> 0:02:13,000
whales, sharks,

43
0:02:14.461,000 --> 0:02:16,000
and even some sea turtles.

44
0:02:17.34,000 --> 0:02:19,000
After two weeks with no human contact,

45
0:02:19.615,000 --> 0:02:21,000
Tori was able to contact a local cargo ship

46
0:02:21.937,000 --> 0:02:23,000
via VHF radio.

47
0:02:24.863,000 --> 0:02:27,000
(Video) TMM: Do you guys have a weather report, over?

48
0:02:28.648,000 --> 0:02:31,000
Man: Heading up to a low

49
0:02:31.782,000 --> 0:02:33,000
ahead of you but it's heading,

50
0:02:34.267,000 --> 0:02:35,000
and you're obviously going northeast

51
0:02:36.147,000 --> 0:02:37,000
and there's a high behind us.

52
0:02:38.051,000 --> 0:02:39,000
That'd be coming

53
0:02:39.909,000 --> 0:02:41,000
east-northeast also.

54
0:02:42.416,000 --> 0:02:43,000
TMM: Good.

55
0:02:44.019,000 --> 0:02:47,000
DL: She's pretty happy to talk to another human at this point.

56
0:02:47.925,000 --> 0:02:49,000
(Video) TMM: So weather report says nothing dramatic

57
