is going to happen soon.

58
0:02:52.98,000 --> 0:02:54,000
DL: What the weather report didn't tell her

59
0:02:54.991,000 --> 0:02:57,000
was that she was rowing right into the path of Hurricane Danielle

60
0:02:58.089,000 --> 0:03:02,000
in the worst hurricane season on record in the North Atlantic.

61
0:03:04.138,000 --> 0:03:06,000
(Video) TMM: Just sprained my ankle.

62
0:03:07.133,000 --> 0:03:1,000
There's a very strong wind from the east now.

63
0:03:10.848,000 --> 0:03:12,000
It's blowing about.

64
0:03:13.286,000 --> 0:03:15,000
It's blowing!

65
0:03:16.165,000 --> 0:03:18,000
After 12 days of storm

66
0:03:18.859,000 --> 0:03:19,000
I get to row for four hours

67
0:03:20.693,000 --> 0:03:22,000
without a flagging wind.

68
0:03:22.837,000 --> 0:03:23,000
I'm not very happy right now.

69
0:03:24.527,000 --> 0:03:25,000
As happy as I was this morning,

70
0:03:26.196,000 --> 0:03:29,000
I am unhappy now, so ...

71
0:03:32.2,000 --> 0:03:33,000
DL: After nearly three months at sea,

72
0:03:34.195,000 --> 0:03:36,000
she'd covered over 3,000 miles.

73
0:03:36.888,000 --> 0:03:38,000
She was two thirds of the way there,

74
0:03:38.908,000 --> 0:03:41,000
but in the storm, the waves were the size of a seven-story building.

75
0:03:42.438,000 --> 0:03:44,000
Her boat kept capsizing.

76
0:03:44.614,000 --> 0:03:47,000
Some of them were pitchpole capsizes, flipping her end over end,

77
0:03:47.818,000 --> 0:03:49,000
and rowing became impossible.

78
