I'm in something big, bad and ugly.

80
0:03:57.06,000 --> 0:03:59,000
Two capsizes.

81
0:03:59.66,000 --> 0:04:04,000
Last capsize, I took the rib off the top of my ceiling with my back.

82
0:04:08.356,000 --> 0:04:11,000
I've had about six capsizes now.

83
0:04:11.839,000 --> 0:04:13,000
The last one was a pitchpole.

84
0:04:14.346,000 --> 0:04:16,000
I have the Argus beacon with me.

85
0:04:17.295,000 --> 0:04:18,000
I would set off the distress signal,

86
0:04:19.083,000 --> 0:04:23,000
but quite frankly, I don't think they'd ever be able to find this little boat.

87
0:04:23.309,000 --> 0:04:24,000
It's so far underwater right now,

88
0:04:25.12,000 --> 0:04:29,000
the only part that's showing pretty much is the cabin.

89
0:04:29.299,000 --> 0:04:32,000
It's about 10 a.m.

90
0:04:32.434,000 --> 0:04:34,000
I've lost track of the number of capsizes.

91
0:04:35.127,000 --> 0:04:38,000
I seem to capsize about every 15 minutes.

92
0:04:38.169,000 --> 0:04:41,000
I think I may have broken my left arm.

93
0:04:45.204,000 --> 0:04:46,000
The waves

94
0:04:46.667,000 --> 0:04:48,000
are tearing the boat to shreds.

95
0:04:50.556,000 --> 0:04:51,000
I keep praying because

96
0:04:52.042,000 --> 0:04:54,000
I'm not sure I'm going to make it through this.

97
0:04:55.128,000 --> 0:04:57,000
DL: Tori set off her distress beacon

98
0:04:57.447,000 --> 0:04:59,000
and was rescued by a passing container ship.

99
0:05:00.341,000 --> 0:05:03,000
They found her abandoned boat two months later adrift near France.

100
0:05:04.325,000 --> 0:05:07,000
I read about it in the newspaper.

101
0:05:07.506,000 --> 0:05:11,000
In 1998, I was a high school student living in Louisville, Kentucky.

102
0:05:11.779,000 --> 0:05:13,000
Now, I live in New York City. I'm a songwriter.

103
0:05:14.333,000 --> 0:05:17,000
And her bravery stuck with me, and I'm adapting her story

104
